title: President Emmerson Mnangagwa Re-elected in Zimbabwe
description: President Emmerson Mnangagwa won another five-year term by intimidating voters and manipulating the campaign process.

title: U.S. Knew Saudis Were Killing African Migrants
description: The United States was told last year that Saudi security forces were shooting, shelling and abusing groups of migrants, but it chose not to raise the issue publicly.

title: New E.U. Climate Change Rules Anger Bloc’s Farmers
description: Asked to cut herds, move or even shut down to help meet E.U. environmental goals, agricultural workers say too much is demanded of them. Their anger is reshaping the political landscape.

title: The Wildfires Are Still Burning, but the Economic Toll Is Becoming Clearer
description: Little economic support is available to evacuees now out of work, insurance disputes loom and economic growth may be eroded.

title: At This Movie, Their Phones Won’t Bother You. Their Barking Might.
description: A cinema chain in Britain is welcoming dogs to select screenings. They don’t need their own tickets, and they don’t need to turn off their cellphones.

title: Ukrainian Commander Urges More Defenses in the Northeast
description: In an apparent break with Pentagon advice, Gen. Oleksandr Syrsky, the commander of Ukraine’s eastern forces, called for “all measures” to defend an area where Russia was threatening to take more territory.

title: Ukraine Is Still Grappling With the Battlefield Prigozhin Left Behind
description: He shored up Russian forces at their most vulnerable and drew Ukraine into a costly fight for Bakhmut, giving Moscow time to build defenses that are slowing Ukraine’s counteroffensive.

title: How China’s Long Arm Nabbed the Dissident Lawyer Lu Siwei
description: Beijing has become more aggressive in its pursuit of dissidents overseas, as highlighted by the arrest of a Chinese rights lawyer in Laos.

title: In New York City, the Chances of Spotting a Rare Bird are on the Rise
description: Sharp-eyed birders might spot brown boobies, a tropical species once rare even in the Southern states. A flock of Canada geese might just include a pink-footed goose, too.

title: Egypt Demolishes Cultural Gems in Cairo in Push to Modernize
description: The Egyptian government has demolished historic tombs, cultural centers, artisan workshops and gardens in pursuit of large-scale urban renewal.

title: How a Judge’s Ruling on Torture Imperils a Guantánamo Prosecution Strategy
description: In dismissing a confession in the bombing of the U.S.S. Cole, Col. Lanny J. Acosta Jr. has shaken a foundation of U.S. government cases at the post-9/11 court.

title: ‘He Has Blood on His Hands’
description: In a Ukraine village, there are no tears for Yevgeny V. Prigozhin, the leader of the Wagner private militia, whose presumed death in a plane crash was reported this week.

title: Spanish Soccer Body Threatens to Sue Over Player’s Account of Kiss
description: The group said it was defending the honor of its president, Luis Rubiales, who kissed the player, Jennifer Hermoso. Players have vowed not to take the field until he resigns.

title: Raimondo Heads to China to Both Promote Trade, and Restrict It
description: The commerce secretary’s trip may be the clearest demonstration yet of the balancing act the Biden administration is trying to pull off in its relations with China.

title: The Eternal Search for the ‘Nemesis Bird’
description: For every devoted birder, there is a bird that continues to elude sighting.
